                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In the area of United Nations Affairs involving non-self-governing territories
                    outside the trusteeship system itself, two questions of interest to the United
                    States are documented here. One relates to the recurring problem of the status
                    of South West Africa. The other concerns the question of information (regarding
                    the non-self-governing territories) transmitted to the United Nations by the
                    administering authorities under Article 73(<hi rend="italic">e</hi>) of the
                    Charter of the United Nations.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
